<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
Abdominal tergites brown, tergite I (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–11" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 11. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 antenna 3 midtarsus, anterior view 4 foretarsus, ventral view 5 foreleg 6 midleg 7 hind leg 8 wing 9 hind tibial comb 10 head, dorsal view 11 abdominal tergite I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361387" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures1-11">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) with lateral tufts of 10-12 short setae arranged in oval area, with anteromesal dark, triangular spot; abdominal segment VIII with a pair of subquadrate genital sclerotations near semi-circular gonopore, ventral hair tufts dark and conspicuous, each comprising a row of four or five long black bristles and a row of four short bristles on each side (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 12–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 12 - 16. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 12 terminal four segments of abdomen, ventral view 13 spermathecae and hair tufts, ventral view 14 proboscis and palpi, anterior view 15 mandibular teeth, anterior view 16 maxillary palpus, anterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361388" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16">Figs 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 12–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 12 - 16. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 12 terminal four segments of abdomen, ventral view 13 spermathecae and hair tufts, ventral view 14 proboscis and palpi, anterior view 15 mandibular teeth, anterior view 16 maxillary palpus, anterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361388" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16">13</figureCitation>
); cerci brown; two dark brown spermathecae, large, oval, unequal, 129
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
83 (109
<normalizedToken originalValue="–129×67–">-129x67-</normalizedToken>
83) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
and 94
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
66 (90
<normalizedToken originalValue="–110×57–">-110x57-</normalizedToken>
66) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, neck absent, and a third vestigial spermatheca present (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 12–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 12 - 16. Female of Nilobezzia bamenwana sp. nov. 12 terminal four segments of abdomen, ventral view 13 spermathecae and hair tufts, ventral view 14 proboscis and palpi, anterior view 15 mandibular teeth, anterior view 16 maxillary palpus, anterior view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/361388" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.893.39032.figures12-16">Figs 12</figureCitation>
, 
